11.15.22  12:48 am   should you finish things that you do not think are good?

     sometimes

     what if you are doing things and you think they are bad, so you move onto doing other things but they are also bad and as a result you finish nothing? how do you finish bad things without hating it?

      if you find yourself never finishing anything, if these feelings sink low enough, it becomes very inspiring to make something like a 10-picture deal with yourself, or something. sign on to an agreement where you are required to make a certain amount of things, understanding that you might not like all of them, but you will finish all of them. a lot can be learned here

If you put the bass on D, it's usually called D13. if you put the bass on Ab, it's called Ab7#9. if the bass is on A, then it might be called Amin6(9)
